<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-11-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Meyer</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-11-06"><hi rend="italic">November 6,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 204.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a
                            copy of an application<note n="a" xml:id="d689fna">Not printed.</note>
                            for a passport presented at the embassy last month before my return. The
                            applicant, Antonio Basile, a boy not yet 12 years old, claimed American
                            citizenship through his father’s naturalization; but as he had never
                            been in the United States Mr. Iddings refused to issue the passport. The
                            case is submitted for your opinion.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">G. V. L. Meyer.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>